[00:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'A brand new open-source 3D air model just dropped called 3 post plat. It generates accurate 3D Gaussian splats from a single image, lets you control exactly how much detail you want, and the best thing is it\'s entirely free and runs on all systems. Today, I\'m going to'

[00:13] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'show you how to run it in ComfyUI, how good the results really are, and how it compares to Trellis too. And the best part, there are no installation scripts [music] needed, no custom nodes, no dependencies. It\'s natively built inside'

[00:27] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'ComfyUI and probably the easiest 3D air setup I\'ve ever shown on this channel. So, let\'s get into it. All [snorts] right, so what is 3 post plat exactly? If you have been following this channel, you know tools like Trellis too that'

[00:40] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'generates 3D meshes from 2D images and generate like triangles, vertices, the kind of 3D model you would then basically use in Blender or a game engine. 3 post plat is here a bit different because 3 post plat generates'

[00:53] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Gaussian splats. You can compare to a sculpture made of clay basically because it has a solid surface and you can touch and reshape it directly. A Gaussian splat is a bit different because it\'s'

[01:05] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'more like a photograph made of thousands of tiny colored dots floating in 3D space. From any angle, it looks quite photoreal, but there\'s no solid surface underneath. This doesn\'t mean that we can\'t use Gaussian splats in production.'

[01:18] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'It\'s great for prototyping, also to visualize 3D scenes, and it\'s especially used in virtual reality and augmented reality. The great thing is as well that I\'m going to show you a ComfyUI workflow which directly generates you Gaussian'

[01:31] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'splat into a 3D mesh that you can then import into Blender. And I\'m going to show you now exactly how to set it up and what you need to take care of. Basically, when we are on the website on'

[01:44] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the GitHub page of 3 post plat, you will basically see here that as a first thing we have an MIT license, which is really great because this basically means that we can use it commercially. It was'

[01:56] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'released by the triple team, so huge shout out here to the researcher team of Best AI basically to release it under an MIT license, which basically means it\'s open source. Super great thing is here as well that it has near to zero'

[02:09] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'dependencies, as you can see here, so it doesn\'t require Transformers, diffusers, or any version conflict hell. So, it runs basically on any platform, which is of course cool because you can use it'

[02:21] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'then under Windows, Linux, and Mac, as well as then on the Nvidia GPUs, and probably even AMD GPUs, even though I didn\'t test it yet myself. In case it works for you with AMD, for all the AMD'

[02:33] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'fans in our community, let us know down below if it works for you. So, let\'s get started with the installation. And to set this up up front because you guys are always wondering about how much VRAM it uses. Right now, it currently stands'

[02:46] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'at default settings around the 8 to 9 GB VRAM mark to generate the Gaussian splat as well as the video and the generated mesh then out of the Gaussian splat. So, definitely keep that in mind while'

[02:58] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'working with it. Probably, when you choose lower settings, you can run it on even less VRAM, but I think at least 8 GB VRAM are recommended for this workflow. In case you use it on six and you get it running, then let us know'

[03:11] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'down below. So, to get started is you can either use like ComfyUI desktop, you can also use ComfyUI portable default, or you use ComfyUI easy install, which I usually use in my videos. In case you would like to set up easy install, I'

[03:24] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'will have a direct link down below for you in the video description. To set it up now is super easy because all the thing we need to do is that we are on the latest ComfyUI version. And to do that is that you can go here to update'

[03:36] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'comfyui.bat that you see over here, and this will then open a terminal which will then update your ComfyUI to the latest version basically. Just make sure that you don\'t execute this one here because this might destroy remaining'

[03:49] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'dependencies that you have from other packages. So, I would always recommend to only use the update-conf.bat file. Once you have this done and it\'s saying here update completed, we can then close this already. Now, we can'

[04:01] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'already start ComfyUI. Just click here on start-conf.bat. All right, and once ComfyUI launched, you will see that we have here a blank'

[04:13] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'window. And now, to actually open a workflow, this is also incredibly easy because it\'s directly implemented into ComfyUI. Only thing you need to do is that you go here to the templates tab over here. Then, you can search here'

[04:25] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'tripo, and then make sure that you scroll down, and then you will see here basically tripo splat image to Gaussian splat. And this is the only workflow we need for this video, so you can directly click on it, and then you will see that'

[04:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
