AUDIO: 'thing is of course that we can also see here that it extracts us here a 3D model from our Gaussian splat which is really amazing of course because this one we can actually then import into blender and use for our project basically. And'

[07:36] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'as you can see this workflow is incredibly fast and delivers really solid results when it comes to that. To import your 3D model is also very easy, so you can go to Blender for example, then make sure that you go to file,'

[07:49] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'import, and then you choose here GLB. Then, once you\'re here in GLB, what you can do is that you navigate to your ComfyUI folder, and once you\'re here in your ComfyUI folder, just make sure that you go to ComfyUI, then output, then'

[08:02] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'here on 3D, and then, as you can see here, we have then have our generated triplesplat file over here. It will be always saved under output and 3D. Then, you can hit here merge vertices already'

[08:14] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'and import [music] GLTF. And then, you will see that we have our generated mesh over here, basically. You will still see that it has sometimes some artifacts around this area here where we get some'

[08:26] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'holes, and that of course the texture itself is not that high-res at the moment. Apart from that, you will see that we have here a quite nice representation on our mesh. We can spin around [music] it, and you will also see'

